{"_id":"uL2ZEbbMpHA3XJpO","name":"Companion's Transformation","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.companion-s-transformation","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have befriended one of OZena's three companions (Lowe, Hirnloser, or Dose) and witnessed their character arc complete: the coward finding courage, the 'brainless' proving genius, or the hollow finding heart through love. Their transformation inspires you. Choose one companion you've built relationship with. Once per scenario, channel their realized virtue: **Lowe's Courage** (reroll any Fear/Intimidation Check, taking better result), **Hirnloser's Genius** (ask GM one specific tactical question—'What's the hidden weakness?' 'What would genius do?'—and receive honest answer), or **Dose's Love** (when protecting someone you care for, +2 to Defense or one automatic success on Protect action). This gift represents how witnessing others' growth helps us find our own strength.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Build meaningful relationship with at least one companion across multiple Parts, witness or facilitate their Part Three transformation</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Can only channel virtue of companion you've actually befriended—can't choose all three. If that companion dies or betrays you before their arc completes, lose this gift. Using this gift in their presence grants them +1 to their next Check (your faith empowers them).</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> inspiration, character-development, virtue, social</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.companion-s-transformation","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["inspiration","character-development","virtue","social"],"requirements":"Build meaningful relationship with at least one companion across multiple Parts, witness or facilitate their Part Three transformation","limitations":"Can only channel virtue of companion you've actually befriended—can't choose all three. If that companion dies or betrays you before their arc completes, lose this gift. Using this gift in their presence grants them +1 to their next Check (your faith empowers them)."},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332109,"modifiedTime":1784280332109,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CbZeN5CDCV4UOWx8","name":"The Wishing Well's Price","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/water/barrier-ice-crystal-wall-jagged-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.the-wishing-well-s-price","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned the truth about Smaragd's Wishing Well: it grants wishes, but corrupts them in cruel ways. The villagers prove this—one wished for wealth and became living gold statue, another for eternal beauty and became porcelain doll, another to never sleep and went mad from exhaustion. You can make ONE wish at the well, but you understand the price. Before wishing, make a Check vs OL Hard (7): on success, phrase your wish carefully enough that corruption is minimized (GM interprets fairly but still with consequence). On failure, wish is granted in most twisted way possible. Alternatively, use your knowledge to resist the well's temptation: once per Scene, when an NPC or enemy tries to use the well, you can intervene and explain the cost—make Social Check to convince them. This represents wisdom to see through false promises.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Investigate the Villagers of Emerald and learn their wish-corruption stories, OR witness Henkle or enemy using the well</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>You can only make ONE wish per campaign—choose wisely. If you wish for something selfless (helping others, stopping Henkle, saving companions), GM should minimize corruption. Selfish wishes corrupt more severely. The well cannot grant impossible wishes (resurrection, time travel without Compass Rose, true love). Some villagers may become hostile if you try to destroy their 'gift' even if it's a curse.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> knowledge, temptation, wishes, wisdom</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.the-wishing-well-s-price","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["knowledge","temptation","wishes","wisdom"],"requirements":"Investigate the Villagers of Emerald and learn their wish-corruption stories, OR witness Henkle or enemy using the well","limitations":"You can only make ONE wish per campaign—choose wisely. If you wish for something selfless (helping others, stopping Henkle, saving companions), GM should minimize corruption. Selfish wishes corrupt more severely. The well cannot grant impossible wishes (resurrection, time travel without Compass Rose, true love). Some villagers may become hostile if you try to destroy their 'gift' even if it's a curse."},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9q1trYho9gtRdi6U","name":"Time Thief","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/time/hourglass-tilted-gray.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.time-thief","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned Henkle's secret: his Hot-Air Balloon is powered by Time Tokens harvested from temporal anomalies caused by the Compass Rose's presence in 1780. You can disrupt his escape plan by stealing or destroying his Time Tokens. Once per Scene, when Henkle would gain a Time Token (combat start, delaying him, Hunters lost in Illusory Labyrinth), make a Check vs his OL (5): on success, you intercept the temporal energy—Henkle gains no Token, and you gain insight into time flow (ask GM one yes/no question about immediate future: 'Will the balloon launch this Scene?' 'Is reinforcement arriving?'). If you accumulate 3 Time Tokens before Henkle does, you can either: sabotage his balloon permanently (it will never fly), or redirect the time portal to send companions home instead of Henkle escaping.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Discover Henkle's Time Token mechanic through investigation, eavesdropping, or studying the Hot-Air Balloon</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Henkle notices when Tokens are stolen—he becomes hostile and focuses on eliminating you. Each stolen Token causes temporal headache (GM may impose -1 to Mental Checks while carrying multiple Tokens). If you die while carrying Tokens, they dissipate harmlessly but Henkle can collect new ones. Redirecting time portal requires having both Tokens AND at least two Compass Rose pieces.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> sabotage, temporal, tactical, counter-villain</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.time-thief","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["sabotage","temporal","tactical","counter-villain"],"requirements":"Discover Henkle's Time Token mechanic through investigation, eavesdropping, or studying the Hot-Air Balloon","limitations":"Henkle notices when Tokens are stolen—he becomes hostile and focuses on eliminating you. Each stolen Token causes temporal headache (GM may impose -1 to Mental Checks while carrying multiple Tokens). If you die while carrying Tokens, they dissipate harmlessly but Henkle can collect new ones. Redirecting time portal requires having both Tokens AND at least two Compass Rose pieces."},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
